values: Definition of -iness in English: -iness suffixɪnəsForming nouns corresponding to adjectives ending in -y (such as clumsiness corresponding to clumsy).OriginSee -y1, -ness.Definition of -iness in US English: -iness suffixForming nouns corresponding to adjectives ending in -y (such as clumsiness corresponding to clumsy).OriginSee -y, -ness.
